What is TA?
  Study of market actions using charts for the purpose of future forecasting, rather than using company's earning report, purely focus on what the   price is doing.
Three core Premisis:
  1.Market action discounts everything: Everything that can affect the price is already there in the chart(Politics, economic ), we dont need to worry why the price is moving, chart has everything. 
  2.Price moves in trend : Identify what the price trend is and go with the flow.
  3.History repeats itself:Human emotions are derived from fear and greed, it wont change so any past charts can be used for training purposes.


DOW Theory
______________

Charles Dow -  Father of technical analysis, his theories still are the corner stone of  modern day trading
  Market has 3 trend accor to DOW
    1.Tide
    2.Wave
    3.Ripple

    Tide - Long term direction of market, often more  than a year
    Wave - Temporary changes in the Tide, last 3w - 3m. If tide is going up, wave can temp pull down the price
    Ripple - Short term, day to day fluctuations

  Tide has 3 phases
    Accumulation phhase - Market price has been dropping- everyone worried - Cunnning investors starts buying the market since bad news happened.
    Public Participation phase - trend followers puts more value in the ongoing trends resulting in a greater boost to the trend.
    Distribution phase -  News spread, everyone rush to buy the stock - investors who bought will sell the shares to latecomers
  

  Volume must confirm trend
    Volume- amount of trading activity done a day.
    Volume should expand as the trend rises, volume should be heavier when in uptrend( Buyers push price higher)

  Trend is assumed to be in effect until chart shows
    Dont assume trend is going to end, analyse chart effectively and predict the upcomings.
